>
  <p>
    Memoato can hold health context, family details, personal metrics, purchases, and the kind of unfinished thoughts
    that never make it into a formal document. That makes privacy a product requirement, not a marketing badge.
  </p>

  <h2>Three storage modes</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cloud sync</strong> — normal server storage and the smoothest multi-device experience.</li>
    <li><strong>Encrypted cloud</strong> — sensitive category titles and notes are encrypted on your device before saving.</li>
    <li><strong>Local-only</strong> — categories and entries stay in the browser on a single device.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Privacy without theatre</h2>
  <p>
    Each mode has a real trade-off. Cloud is convenient. Encrypted cloud protects selected content but requires a
    passphrase that Memoato cannot recover. Local-only keeps data off the server but makes the device and its browser
    storage your only copy.
  </p>

  <p>Read the exact behavior and service providers in the <a href="/privacy">privacy policy</a>.</p>

